    <title type="html"><![CDATA[Vim Panes]]></title>
    <link href="http://d-kunin.github.io/blog/2016/02/26/vim-panes/"/>
    <updated>2016-02-26T16:52:58-08:00</updated>
    <id>http://d-kunin.github.io/blog/2016/02/26/vim-panes</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<ul>
<li><code>Ctrl-W, s</code> will create a horizontal split.</li>
<li><code>Ctrl-W, v</code> will create a vertical split.</li>
<li><code>Ctrl-W, direction</code> will allow you to move among the panes.</li>
<li><code>:ls</code> will show your open buffers.</li>
<li><code>:b &lt;number&gt;</code> will open the specified buffer in the current pane.</li>
</ul>


<p>Based on <a href="https://www.quora.com/How-do-I-switch-between-panes-in-split-mode-in-Vim">Quora Answer by Deniel Lo</a>.</p>
]]></content>
